cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about representation learning for sequence tagging in natural language processing (NLP), which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of deep models and multi-task learning suggests that it may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on named entity recognition and information retrieval suggests that it may also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
